<br>
<center>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">2025 March 01 - 02:   Annual aikido seminar in Cebu City</span>
</center>
<br>
<br><br>

With support and encouragement of Aikido Philippines (AP), Filipino Federation of Aikido (FFA), and Philippine Aikido Propagation Association (PAPA), the annual aikido seminar for 2025, traditionally led by a Hombu Dojo instructor, will be held at City Sports Club Cebu in Cebu City Philippines from <b>March 1 to 2, 2025</b>.<br><br>

The event this year will be hosted by SHACC in celebration of its 20th anniversary. SHACC has been a member of FFA since its founding.<br><br>

The year 2025 also marks the 10th anniversary of the Visayas Aikido Fellowship (VAF), an annual interclub fellowship of the Visayas Region aikidoists.<br><br> 

Leading the seminar will be Hiroshi Fujimaki Shihan, 7th dan, from Japan Aikikai Hombu Dojo<br><br><br>


<center>
________________________________________________
</center>

<br><br>

The Makati Aikido Club, represented by volunteer members, participated in the 20th anniversary celebration of the Sacred Heart Aikido Center Cebu (SHACC) and the 10th anniversary of the Visayas Aikido Fellowship.<br><br>

Fujimaki Hiroshi Shihan (7th Dan) of the Aikikai Foundation, led six seminar sessions, gave a demonstration, and conducted promotion examinations for candidates seeking black belt and higher rankings.<br><br>

Additionally, on the first day of the event, His Excellency Consul General Hideaki Matsuo, along with his wife Kanami and dignitaries from the Japanese Embassy in Cebu, attended the celebration, adding to the significance of the gathering.<br><br><br>

